Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
checkUnique(25.10)                                          checkUnique(25.10)

Name
       checkUnique - Checks the uniqueness of the netlist

Syntax
       checkUnique

       [-help]

       [-verbose]

       Checks  the  uniqueness of the netlist. Certain features, such as clock
       tree synthesis and IPO, require a module (a non-leaf cell)  to  be  in-
       stantiated only once. If the netlist is unique, the result is 1; other-
       wise, the result is 0.

       You can use the checkUnique command after importing a design.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each checkUnique parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man checkUnique.

       -verbose
              Displays the names of modules instantiated more than once.

Example
       The following command checks the uniqueness of the netlist and displays
       the names of any modules instantiate more than once:

       innovus 4> checkUnique -verbose

       The sample output is as shown below:

       Non-leaf cell A instantiated 2 times.

       0

